## 3пёҸвғЈ [mobile_client.html](file:///d:/Project/Smart%20Path%20Suggestor/mobile_client.html) вҖ” The Phone Interface

> **What it does**: Runs **entirely in the phone's browser**. Captures camera frames, sends them to the server, and provides voice + vibration feedback to the user.

### How the Phone Connects

1. User opens `http://LAPTOP_IP:5000/` on phone browser
2. Server serves [mobile_client.html](file:///d:/Project/Smart%20Path%20Suggestor/mobile_client.html)
3. The HTML/JS app runs entirely in the browser

```python
# In server.py:
@app.route("/", methods=["GET"])
def mobile_client():
    return send_file("mobile_client.html")
```

### Camera Initialization

```javascript
async function startCamera() {
    const stream = await navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia({
        video: {
            facingMode: "environment",   // Rear camera (back-facing)
            width: { ideal: 640 },
            height: { ideal: 480 },
        }
    });
    video.srcObject = stream;
}
```

### Frame Capture & Send Loop

Every **500ms** (2 detections/second), the app captures a frame and sends it:

```javascript
const DETECT_INTERVAL_MS = 500;
const JPEG_QUALITY = 0.65;
const CAPTURE_WIDTH = 320;
const CAPTURE_HEIGHT = 240;

function captureFrame() {
    canvas.width = CAPTURE_WIDTH;
    canvas.height = CAPTURE_HEIGHT;
    ctx.drawImage(video, 0, 0, CAPTURE_WIDTH, CAPTURE_HEIGHT);

    // Convert to Base64 JPEG (strip prefix)
    const dataURL = canvas.toDataURL("image/jpeg", JPEG_QUALITY);
    return dataURL.split(",")[1];   // Remove "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
}

async function sendFrame() {
    const b64Frame = captureFrame();

    const response = await fetch(`${SERVER_URL}/detect`, {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({ image: b64Frame }),
        signal: AbortSignal.timeout(3000)   // 3 second timeout
    });

    const data = await response.json();
    handleResult(data);
}

// Start the loop when user taps START
intervalId = setInterval(sendFrame, DETECT_INTERVAL_MS);
```

### Voice Output (Text-to-Speech)

```javascript
function speak(message, priority) {
    if (isMuted) return;

    // Only CRITICAL messages can interrupt ongoing speech
    if (isSpeaking && priority !== "CRITICAL") return;

    synth.cancel();   // Stop current speech

    const utter = new SpeechSynthesisUtterance(message);
    utter.rate   = priority === "CRITICAL" ? 1.3 : 1.1;  // Faster for critical
    utter.pitch  = priority === "CRITICAL" ? 1.2 : 1.0;  // Higher pitch = urgency
    utter.volume = 1.0;

    synth.speak(utter);
}
```

### Vibration Feedback

```javascript
// Server sends alert_pattern like [300, 100, 300]
if (vibEnabled && alertPat.length > 0 && navigator.vibrate) {
    navigator.vibrate(alertPat);   // Browser Vibration API
}
```

### UI Components

The mobile client has these visual elements:

| Component | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| **Camera preview** | Live `<video>` feed from rear camera |
| **Status box** | Shows current voice message, color-coded by priority |
| **Zone display** | 5 blocks showing risk level per zone (color: green/yellow/red) |
| **Detections list** | Top 5 detected objects with distance and zone |
| **Control buttons** | START, STOP, MUTE voice, toggle vibration |
| **Stats bar** | Connection status, latency, requests/second |

### Screen Wake Lock

Prevents the phone screen from sleeping during navigation:

```javascript
let wakeLock = null;
async function requestWakeLock() {
    wakeLock = await navigator.wakeLock.request("screen");
}
requestWakeLock();

// Re-acquire when page becomes visible again
document.addEventListener("visibilitychange", () => {
    if (document.visibilityState === "visible") requestWakeLock();
});
```

