## 4пёҸвғЈ [detection_local.py](file:///d:/Project/Smart%20Path%20Suggestor/detection_local.py) вҖ” Standalone Local Mode

> **What it does**: Runs the same detection pipeline **entirely on the laptop** using the built-in webcam. No phone or server needed. Uses `winsound.Beep()` for audio alerts.

```python
# Camera setup (laptop webcam)
cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0, cv2.CAP_DSHOW)

while True:
    ret, frame = cap.read()
    frame = cv2.resize(frame, (480, 360))

    # Run YOLO + MiDaS every 8th frame (for performance)
    if frame_count % 8 == 0:
        results = model(frame, imgsz=480, verbose=False)
        cached_boxes = results[0].boxes

        input_batch = transform(img_rgb).to(device)
        with torch.no_grad():
            prediction = midas(input_batch)
            # ... interpolate to match frame size
        cached_depth_map = prediction.cpu().numpy()

    # Draw bounding boxes + distance labels
    for box in cached_boxes:
        cv2.rectangle(frame, (x1, y1), (x2, y2), (0, 255, 0), 2)
        cv2.putText(frame, f"{label} {distance_m:.2f}m", ...)

    # Beep alert when object < 0.5 meters
    if danger_detected and (current_time - last_beep_time > BEEP_COOLDOWN):
        winsound.Beep(1000, 300)   # 1000Hz for 300ms

    cv2.imshow("Smart Path - Beep Alert", frame)
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Key difference from server mode**: Local mode processes only every **8th frame** to maintain performance on a single machine, while server mode processes every frame received (phone sends every 500ms).

