## рҹ§¬ Key Algorithms Summary

### 1. Depth Estimation (MiDaS Calibration)
```
real_distance = SCALE / midas_depth_value
where SCALE = known_real_distance Г— midas_value_at_that_distance
```

### 2. Risk Scoring
```
risk = object_weight Г— proximity_factor Г— vertical_multiplier
     = PRIORITY_WEIGHTS[label] Г— min(1.0, 2.0/(distance+0.1)) Г— {bottom:2, middle:1.2, top:0.7}
```

### 3. Zone Assignment (Numeric Regions)
```
Frame divided into 5 regions: -2, -1, 0, +1, +2 (20% each)
Region 0 = center walking path (full alerts)
Region Вұ1 = near-side (max WARN, short beep)
Region Вұ2 = far-side (max GUIDE, directional beep only)
Left beep = 400 Hz, Right beep = 800 Hz
```

### 4. Object Stability
```
Object must appear in 3 consecutive frames вҶ’ "stable"
Distance averaged across frames for smoothness
Stale objects (not seen for 2s) are removed
```

### 5. Zone Smoothing
```
Majority vote over last 5 frames
Need 60% agreement to switch safe zone
Prevents confusing "left-center-left-center" flickering
```

